csum=As much as we believe in Tian, the concepts behind Tian have never been done before and are thus quite experimental.  That said, the monetary theories behind Tian are, I would argue, less risky than those behind Bitcoin which is based on deflation which actually has been tried in the past and has never worked out.  Basically deflation is the symptom of a Monetary Policy that cannot keep up with the economy [[https://www.investopedia.com/articles/investing/030915/top-6-ways-governments-fight-deflation.asp|#]]. Tian is a non-centralized, formulaically adjustable monetary policy which is set in stone. 
