diff:1623688449:1623521540:=82c82%0a%3c In terms of the name of a unit of the currency, it is one Tian or 5 Tian.  The currency is broken down with 3 decimal places, so 1 Tian will be 1.000 Tian.  The smallest unit of the currency is a Di, pronounced "Dee".  So 1 Tian is 1000 Di.  Two years after launch everyone on the planet could own 125 Tian on average which is 125,000 Di.%0a---%0a> In terms of the name of a unit of the currency, it is one Tian or 5 Tian.  The currency is broken down with 3 decimal places, so 1 Tian will be 1.000 Tian.  The smallest unit of the currency is a Rta, pronounced Rita.  So 1 Tian is 1000 Rta.  Two years after launch everyone on the planet could own 125 Tian on average which is 125,000 Rta.%0a
