diff:1623521540:1623395983:=78c78%0a%3c [[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tian#Chinese_interpretations|Tian]] is a Chinese philosophical concept for "Heaven" or "Order of the Cosmos" and I think that fits with the token purpose.  The ticker [[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%25E1%25B9%259Ata|RTA]] (pronounced "Rita") is an Indian philosophical principle [[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bNM8sEvPLEs|#]] [[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rh3HgUscMYM|#]] [[https://www.yogavedainstitute.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/RTA_and_DHARMA.pdf|#]] meaning "Natural Order".  Tian (Ti天an) is also similar to the word "Titan", namely one named [[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Themis|Themis]], the Greek goddess of Divine Order and Natural Law.%0a---%0a> [[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tian#Chinese_interpretations|Tian]] is a Chinese philosophical concept for "Heaven" or "Order of the Cosmos" and I think that fits with the token purpose.  The ticker [[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%25E1%25B9%259Ata|RTA]] (pronounced "Rita") is an Indian philosophical principle [[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bNM8sEvPLEs|#]] [[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rh3HgUscMYM|#]] meaning "Natural Order".  Tian (Ti天an) is also similar to the word "Titan", namely one named [[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Themis|Themis]], the Greek goddess of Divine Order and Natural Law.%0a
