diff:1623237858:1623237499:=84c84%0a%3c In Tian we decide to scale the new token creation with trading volume.  Once a month, all the volume of trading is multiplied by the fee of 0.1%25 in our case, and that fee in tokens is distributed proportionally to all the current holders of tokens.  If the daily volume is 10%25 of the marketcap on average, after a year a person's token holdings will increase by 3.65%25.  For every token redistrubuted like this, there is an equivalent token created fresh, owned by noone, and put up for sale on the swap.  This means that printing new tokens does not dilute the ownership share of current holders.%0a---%0a> In Tian we decide to scale the new token creation with trading volume.%0a
