diff:1623192531:1623192371:=32c32%0a%3c What if we could balance the amount of new money created with the amount of money that is going to the current token holders?  If this were possible then people would not need to use workarounds to maintain their value while also the economy can grow from an expanding money supply.  Buyers of a currency want the price to be low [[https://www.investopedia.com/articles/investing/090215/3-reasons-why-countries-devalue-their-currency.asp|#]] [[https://www.investopedia.com/ask/answers/what-stock-split-why-do-stocks-split/|#]].  Thus we can keep the price low by expanding the money supply, while also proportionally increasing the number of tokens that holders have; using DeFi trading fees.%0a---%0a> What if we could balance the amount of new money created with the amount of money that is going to the current currency holders?  If this were possible then people would not need to use workarounds to maintain their value while also the economy can grow from an expanding money supply.  Buyers of a currency want the price to be low [[https://www.investopedia.com/articles/investing/090215/3-reasons-why-countries-devalue-their-currency.asp|#]] [[https://www.investopedia.com/ask/answers/what-stock-split-why-do-stocks-split/|#]].  Thus we can keep the price low by expanding the money supply, while also proportionally increasing the number of tokens that holders have; using DeFi trading fees.%0a
