diff:1623008487:1623007728:=37,52c37%0a%3c [[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tian#Chinese_interpretations|Tian]] is a Chinese philosophical concept for "Heaven" or "Order of the Cosmos" and I think that fits with the token purpose.  Also the ticker [[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%25E1%25B9%259Ata|RTA]] (pronounced "Rita") is an Indian philosophical principle [[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bNM8sEvPLEs|#]] meaning "Natural Order".  Tian is also similar to the word "Titan", namely one named [[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Themis|Themis]], the Greek goddess of Divine Order and Natural Law.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Scaling Emission with Trading Volume?%0a%3c %0a%3c In Tian we decide to scale the new token creation with trading volume.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Why create new tokens at all?%0a%3c %0a%3c We want to create new tokens to give new people the opportunity to own tokens improving the distribution of the coins.  The more people hold coins, the more resistant it is to pump and dumps and the more stable the price.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!How do we determine how many tokens to make new?%0a%3c %0a%3c There are many criteria that could be used to determine how many new tokens to create.  With Tether (USDT) they create new tokens based on the value of the coin; to maintain a stable value relative to another currency, the US Dollar.  Thus maintaining a certain price per token is a good way to tune how many new coins are created.  However there are downsides to this.  Firstly the true value of USD is not constant, currently in 2021 we are experiencing over 20%25 increase of USD to the supply which may cause very high inflation.  Secondly backing a token with a governmental commodity like this opens the doors for regulation, the US government is forcing Tether to have a dollar in reserve for each tether minted.  This means that if the Tether corporation ever lacks funds for whatever reason, the Token suffer severe consequences.%0a%3c %0a%3c With Tian we look to a wholly decentralized way to maintain constant value.  Instead of trying to maintain a stable price, we instead try to maintain liquidity.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> [[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tian#Chinese_interpretations|Tian]] is a Chinese philosophical concept for "Heaven" or "Order of the Cosmos" and I think that fits with the token purpose.  Also the ticker [[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%25E1%25B9%259Ata|RTA]] (pronounced "Rita") is an Indian philosophical principle [[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bNM8sEvPLEs|#]] meaning "Natural Order".  Tian is also similar to the word "Titan", namely one named [[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Themis|Themis]], the Greek goddess of Divine Order and Natural Law.%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
